    <stitle>RADIATOR SHUTTERS - OPERATION - SHUTTERS ON VEHICLES WITH ON/OFF FAN DRIVE CLUTCH</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="2">
        <title>SHUTTERS ON VEHICLES WITH ON/OFF FAN DRIVE CLUTCH</title>
        <para>On a vehicle equipped with an ON/OFF fan drive clutch, the shutters must ALWAYS BE OPEN BEFORE the fan
            drive clutch is engaged. Refer to GROUP 12-ENGINE, FAN DRIVE CLUTCH in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>A vehicle having a grill-mounted freon air conditioning condenser with shutters and an ON/OFF fan
                    clutch requires a fan clutch override. Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1200505">Figure 5</hotlnk>and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1200506">Figure 6</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
